00:23:27.570 --> 00:23:29.400 align:middle line:84%
And the significance
is profound,

00:23:29.400 --> 00:23:31.860 align:middle line:84%
because if a snail keeps
moving in a spiral,

00:23:31.860 --> 00:23:33.990 align:middle line:84%
it never crosses
over its own tracks.

00:23:33.990 --> 00:23:36.330 align:middle line:84%
It's always getting
fresh material

00:23:36.330 --> 00:23:38.940 align:middle line:84%
as it's moving through
its environment.

00:23:38.940 --> 00:23:42.480 align:middle line:84%
Well, they did an experiment
where they had a track that

00:23:42.480 --> 00:23:45.840 align:middle line:84%
turned into a Y. And
what they would do

00:23:45.840 --> 00:23:49.080 align:middle line:84%
is put a snail at the
beginning of the track,

00:23:49.080 --> 00:23:52.050 align:middle line:84%
and when it got down to
the branch, to the Y,

00:23:52.050 --> 00:23:55.050 align:middle line:84%
it turned out the snail
always went to the right.

00:23:55.050 --> 00:23:57.030 align:middle line:84%
Well, that was the
movement of the spiral.

00:23:57.030 --> 00:23:58.830 align:middle line:84%
The spiral was always
to go to the right,

00:23:58.830 --> 00:24:01.410 align:middle line:90%
so that's what they anticipated.

00:24:01.410 --> 00:24:03.570 align:middle line:84%
But it turned out that
during the experiments,

00:24:03.570 --> 00:24:07.210 align:middle line:84%
there were times where the
snail would end up going 50-50.

00:24:07.210 --> 00:24:10.110 align:middle line:84%
50% to the right,
and 50% to the left.

00:24:10.110 --> 00:24:12.130 align:middle line:84%
And they said, well,
